  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photographic plate</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1920-1935</date>
      <persName role="Press Photographer Vreme"><forename>Svetozar </forename><surname>Grdijan</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.d2666bab">Grdijan, Svetozar </ref><certainty target="persName" cert="medium" locus="value" /></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Outdoor group portrait of fifteen young girls posing in front of a staircase leading from a courtyard to a house entrance. The girls are dressed for a festive occasion, wearing predominantly dark dresses and carefully done <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B15">Bubikopf</ref> hairstyles. They are standing in two rows: the girls in the front are more concentrated on posing than those in the back, who are either hidden by their colleagues or chatting. A girl on the staircase is watching the scene, her cardigan and less neatly dressed hair indicate that she does not belong to the group.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The girls are probably secondary school pupils on the occasion of their graduation.</ab>
